==English==

===Etymology===
From Greek [[μετάνοια]] (repentance), compounded from the preposition [[μετά]] (after, with) and the verb [[νοέω]] (to perceive, to think).

===Noun===
'''metanoia'''

# A "change of mind." To be saved by Jesus Christ, one must first change their mind as what they deem is correct and willing to choose to trust in Christ for salvation. In English the closest word to "metanoia" is "repentance." However, the word "repentance" has many inaccuracies. The word repentance implies a "turning away from sin" or a form of penance. This is an incorrect interpertation of biblical doctrine. One must first change his mind (metanoia), accept Jesus Christ as savior, then choose to change his life through the power of God.